  "prompt": "What do you need to do to get into Harvard?",
  "response": "To get into Harvard, you typically need:\n\n1. Academic Excellence\n- Near-perfect high school GPA (usually 4.0 or close)\n- Extremely high standardized test scores (SAT around 1500+, ACT around 34+)\n- Challenging course load with many AP/honors classes\n\n2. Outstanding Extracurricular Activities\n- Leadership roles\n- Significant achievements\n- Depth of involvement in activities\n- Unique accomplishments\n\n3. Strong Personal Qualities\n- Demonstrated passion\n- Community service\n- Intellectual curiosity\n- Well-rounded personality\n\n4. Exceptional Application\n- Compelling personal essay\n- Strong letters of recommendation\n- Clear narrative about your goals and achievements\n\n5. Additional Considerations\n- Potential diversity contributions\n- Special talents (athletics, arts, research)\n- Demonstrated potential to make significant contributions\n\n6. Financial Considerations\n- Need-blind admissions\n- Strong financial aid programs for qualified students\n\nThe acceptance rate is typically around 4-5%, making Harvard extremely competitive. No single factor guarantees admission, but excelling in most of these areas significantly improves your chances.",
